🐍 Python Introduction – Easy Notes

📌 What is Python?
Python is a programming language.
It was created by Guido van Rossum in 1991.
It is one of the most popular and easy-to-learn languages today.
💡 Where is Python used?

Python is used in many areas:

🌐 Web Development (backend websites)
💻 Software Development
📊 Data Analysis & Mathematics
⚙️ Automation / System Scripting
🤖 AI & Machine Learning

⚙️ What can Python do?

Python is very powerful. It can:

Build web applications
Automates tasks and workflows
Connect to databases
Read and write files
Handle big data
Perform complex calculations
Help in rapid prototyping (quick project building)

🚀 Why choose Python?
✅ Works on all platforms (Windows, Mac, Linux, etc.)
✅ Simple and easy-to-read syntax (like English)
✅ Requires less code compared to other languages
✅ Runs instantly (no need to compile)
✅ Supports different programming styles:
Procedural
Object-Oriented
Functional

