🔤 Python Syntax (Important)
Python uses new lines to finish commands
(No need for semicolons ;)
Python uses indentation (spaces) to define blocks of code
(instead of {} like other languages)

Example:
if 5 > 2:
    print("5 is greater than 2")

👉 Here, the space before print() is indentation, and it's very important in Python.

🎯 Key Takeaways
Python is easy, powerful, and beginner-friendly
It is used in almost every tech field
Its simple syntax makes coding faster and easier
